post_text:
AUDUBON SCHOOL RECEIVES GENEROUS GIFT

The Audubon Community School was recently the benefactor of a generous gift. 1992 graduate, Jeanette LaFoy, passed away on April 1, 2019. In her will, she left her home in Washington State to the district. The home has been sold and the district received a check for $191,000.

There are no definitive plans for the money at this point. However, the district administration and Board would like to use the money for specific projects that have a direct effect on students and can be credited to Jeanette. The district is very appreciative of this generous gift and is committed to using it to make a positive impact.

Photograph: Board President Mark Nissen, Jeanette's Aunt Denise England, Superintendent Eric Trager

Surplus Property Sealed Bid Auction
The Audubon Community School Board has declared the following property as surplus. It will be sold on a sealed bid auction during the week of July 20, 2020.

Property can be inspected and bids placed at the Agriculture Shop on the south side of the High School building. Inspections and bidding is from 8:00am-3:00pm Monday, July 20 through Wednesday, July 22. Winning bidders will be notified by Friday, July 24. Property must be paid for and removed by Tuesday, July 28, 2020.

Desks, Tables, Chairs, TV, VCR, DVD player, File Cabinet, podium, cart, kitchen ware, plaques, trophies, typewriter, shelving

Items in totes or boxes will be sold by the tote/box full.*

2020-2021 Registration
JMC On-line registration is not ready yet, we are still working on some paperwork with the state for a couple new programs. Notices will go out when that is up and ready in mid-late July. We apologize for the delay, thank you for your patience.

On-line registration is highly recommended, however, If you don't have on-line access, you can pick up forms and pay your fees at the walk-in registration on Tuesday, August 4 (11am-1pm & 4-6pm) in the MS/HS Boardroom. Seniors or parent, please text Jennifer at 515-745-0522 to set the day and time up that works best for you!

NO SACK LUNCH HAND OUT FRIDAY, APRIL 10 due to Good Friday schedule day off from school.

Grab 'n Go Sack Meals program has been extended through April 30.

We are making a few changes, starting Monday, April 13:
Pick up will be Monday & Wednesday only, receiving meals for multiple days at each pick up.

*Pickup will be in Audubon 11:30-12:30
Hamlin 11:30-12:00
Gray 11:30-11:40
Ross 11:45-12:00
*Please make sure to have your front passenger seat open for the workers to put meals inside the window to minimize contact. It would be useful to have a box or laundry basket in the seat to put the meals in as you will be receiving meals for multiple days.

post_text:
MS/HS School Improvement
BOND REFERENDUM VOTING INFORMATION
The question on the ballot will read as follows:
“Shall the Board of Directors of the Audubon Community School District in the Counties of Audubon and Guthrie, State of Iowa, be authorized to contract indebtedness and issue General Obligation Bonds in an amount not to exceed $7,500,000 to provide funds to remodel, repair, and improve the middle school / high school building, including HVAC, electrical, and plumbing improvements?”
**By voting YES for the referendum, residents are giving the district permission to borrow funds for the project.
**By voting NO for the referendum, residents are not giving the district permission to borrow funds for the project.

Any registered voter living within the Audubon School District boundaries is eligible to participate in the election. Election day will be Tuesday, March 3rd, with the polls open from 7:00 am to 8:00 pm at the Agri-Hall for Audubon County Residents.
Guthrie County residents in the Audubon school district will vote at Christian Church in Guthrie Center.

K-12 Audubon Art
January 31 at 2:10 PM ·

Huge congratulations to Clare C. & Abby Z. for winning GOLD Keys from the Scholastic Art Competition!

The Scholastic Art Competition is one of the country’s longest running and most prestigious recognition program for creative students in grades 7-12. The Iowa and Midwest region received over 7,000 pieces of art and writing. Out of those 7,000 pieces, Gold Keys are only awarded to the top 5% of entries!

Gold Key works of art will also have the opportunity to be judged on a national level - national gold medalists will be announced in March.

Scholastic awards are very competitive and only the best artists win awards! I am so lucky to have these girls as students!

I also want to point out that Clare has won an award from Scholastic for the past 3 years! How awesome!
10th grade - Honorable Mention
11th grade - Silver 🔑
12th grade - GOLD 🔑

The food pantry is stocked and ready!
It is located outside the Activity Center door of the High School on the North side of the building. You will find food and some personal care items. Please take what you need.
If you would like to leave items we have attached a list for these cold temps. As it warms up we will provide another list. Items may be left in the superintendents office or in the box itself.
If you know someone in the community in need of food or personal care items please encourage them to check here. It is free to whoever needs it.
If you have questions, please contact Jill Hermansen RN, NCSN, Home and School Liaison
Email: jherm@audubon.k12.ia.us
Phone: 712-563-2607 High School or 712-563-3751 Elementary

shared_text:
Guthrie County REC
January 15 at 11:12 AM ·

Guthrie County REC delivered STEM kits to the Audubon Middle School last week to help students learn more about electricity and renewable energy. We have 10 schools in our service territory that we have been donating STEM kits to and each school has selected unique kits to fit their curriculum needs. This project was funded by CIPCO, Guthrie County REC's power supplier, through an energy efficiency program.

Pictured is Audubon Science Teacher Kim Subbert.

We are proud to help students learn more about the changing energy landscape and their potential roles within it.

Special Education Associate
- Elementary Long-Term Substitute

The Audubon Community School District is looking for compassionate, caring individuals to work as educational associates in our special education program. Candidates need to have a minimum of a high school diploma and the ability to work with students individually and in a small group setting. Past experience working with children with special needs in an educational setting is a plus. The selected candidates will start within the next month to cover an 8-week maternity leave.

The School District does require a background check on all employees.

For more information or to pick up an application form please contact or stop by the Superintendent’s office:
Carla Christensen, Human Resources Director
800 Third Ave.
Audubon, IA 50025
712/563-2607
cchristensen@audubon.k12.ia.us
